                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 22: A bill to raise the ceiling of gratuity for employees to Rs 10 lakh from the present level of Rs 3.5 lakh was introduced in the Lok Sabha today. The Payment of Gratuity (Amendment) Bill 2010, introduced by minister state for labour Harish Rawat, seeks to amend the gratuity act.                             
	 Mumbai, April 22: Rallis India has announced a 1:2 bonus issue and a final dividend of 10 per cent following improved performance. The firm has posted a higher net profit of Rs 22 crore for the fourth quarter of 2009-10 against Rs 10 crore a year ago.                             
	 Mumbai, April 22: Jet Airways will offer business-class seats at highly concessional rates on its all-economy service Jet Konnect from Monday. Under this offer, a business class one-way Delhi-Mumbai ticket on Jet Konnect will cost just Rs 12,000.                            
	 New Delhi, April 22: Reliance Industries and its US partner Atlas Energy have acquired 42,344 acres in the gas-rich Marcellus shale for about $192 million. Reliance had earlier bought a 40 per cent stake in about 3,00,000 acres Marcellus shale gas project of Atlas for $1.7 billion.                                                                                                                          
